  "prompt": "What is the heavy feeling near the larynx which one feels when he or she is feeling guilty, sad or depressed?",
  "response": "The heavy feeling near the larynx that you describe is often referred to as a **\"lump in the throat\"** or **globus sensation**. This sensation is commonly associated with strong emotions such as guilt, sadness, anxiety, or depression. While the exact cause is not fully understood, it is thought to be linked to the tightening of muscles in the throat (such as the cricopharyngeus muscle) due to stress or emotional tension. Additionally, the autonomic nervous system, which is activated during emotional distress, can contribute to this sensation by causing changes in muscle tension and swallowing patterns.\n\nThe lump in the throat is usually harmless and temporary, but if it persists or is accompanied by other symptoms like pain, difficulty swallowing, or hoarseness, it\u2019s a good idea to consult a healthcare professional to rule out any underlying physical causes.",
